You could utilize CSS media queries to adapt your site to different screen sizes:
https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_rwd_mediaqueries.asp

Using media queries, you can define breakpoints like this:

```
a {
 font-size: 1rem;
}

@media screen and (max-width: 700px) {
 a {
  font-size: 0.5rem;
 }
}

```
In this example, you&#39;re instructing the browser to apply a font size of 0.5rem to anchor tags when the viewport width is less than 700px.

